Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum scored 26 points in the first half, making five three-pointers, and leading the Celtics to a 22-point cushion.
The Celtics outrebounded the Hawks 50-43, leading to eight second-chance points for Boston.
Boston intercepted the leather 15 times, putting on a show on the defensive end, and recording seven blocks.
The Celtics tallied 35 fast break points compared to Atlanta's four.
Post-Match Reflections: The Celtics will look to collect their fourth consecutive NBA victory on November 7, 2024, when they seek to protect their home court against Stephen Curry and the Golden State Warriors.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Celtics bombarded Atlanta with 18 drained three-pointers.
Jayson Tatum had a near triple-double performance with 26 points, nine assists, six rebounds, and two steals.
Derrick White joined Tatum in eclipsing the 20-point mark with 21 points, six rebounds, six assists, two steals, and a block.
Payton Pritchard scored 18 markers built from three treys and four field goals from the perimeter.
